==English==

===Etymology===
Borrowed from {{bor|en|es|gringo}}, from {{m|es|griego||Greek}}, used for anyone who spoke an unintelligible language. {{doublet|en|Greek}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ɡɹɪŋɡəʊ/}}
* {{audio|en|En-au-gringo.ogg|Audio (AU)}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɪŋɡəʊ|s=2}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|gringoes}}

# {{lb|en|slang|often|pejorative}} A [[white]] person from an [[English]]-speaking [[country]], particularly the [[United States]].
#* '''2017''', B. M. Bower, ''The Gringos: The Tale of the California Gold Rush Days''
#*: Truly it is as Don José tells me; these '''gringos''' have come but to make trouble where all was peace.

